1
00:00:01,440 --> 00:00:03,120
Did the doctor delay your appointment?

2
00:00:03,200 --> 00:00:04,480
You're late today.

3
00:00:05,000 --> 00:00:07,280
No, it was just the usual schedule.

4
00:00:10,400 --> 00:00:12,680
Did no one come to see me today?

5
00:00:15,200 --> 00:00:16,520
No one.

6
00:00:16,600 --> 00:00:19,400
ONE HOUR EARLIER

7
00:00:28,760 --> 00:00:30,560
- Who did it?
- Hurry up.

8
00:00:37,680 --> 00:00:38,760
Hello, Anong.

9
00:00:38,840 --> 00:00:41,800
Hello. Are you passing by this area?

10
00:00:41,880 --> 00:00:44,880
No. I actually have
an appointment with Sarut.

11
00:00:56,000 --> 00:00:57,840
Then please, come inside.

12
00:03:26,480 --> 00:03:27,680
Here, have some water.

13
00:03:30,560 --> 00:03:34,720
Actually, no one will be here today.

14
00:03:34,800 --> 00:03:37,680
I'm going to visit my nephew
at the hospital.

15
00:03:38,200 --> 00:03:42,040
And Mr. Rut has an appointment
for physical therapy.

16
00:03:42,120 --> 00:03:45,480
Yes, I know.
But I happened to arrive early.

17
00:03:56,560 --> 00:03:57,520
Let me refill your glass.

18
00:04:03,040 --> 00:04:03,880
Anong.

19
00:04:05,360 --> 00:04:06,600
Well…

20
00:04:07,200 --> 00:04:08,560
What happened to your face?

21
00:04:12,040 --> 00:04:15,200
You mean here?

22
00:04:15,280 --> 00:04:18,600
I'm asking seriously.
Did you get into a fight with someone?

23
00:04:19,120 --> 00:04:21,200
Yesterday, I saw you.

24
00:04:27,800 --> 00:04:29,360
No.

25
00:04:29,440 --> 00:04:31,480
I didn't fight with anyone.

26
00:04:32,080 --> 00:04:35,680
If that's the case,
then why does your face look like that?

27
00:04:37,240 --> 00:04:38,920
Do you really want to know?

28
00:04:39,520 --> 00:04:43,560
Actually, Sarut told me
not to tell anyone why I came here.

29
00:04:44,080 --> 00:04:45,760
But I happened to see you.

30
00:04:47,760 --> 00:04:48,760
That's good.

31
00:04:48,840 --> 00:04:51,120
So what exactly happened?

32
00:04:52,680 --> 00:04:53,920
That day,

33
00:04:55,440 --> 00:04:57,720
I met up with someone.

34
00:05:01,040 --> 00:05:03,160
Then I slapped him.

35
00:05:03,240 --> 00:05:04,360
- Like this.
- Ow!

36
00:05:04,440 --> 00:05:06,760
Then I asked him, "Does it hurt?"

37
00:05:07,280 --> 00:05:08,480
What are you doing?

38
00:05:10,840 --> 00:05:11,560
- Does it hurt?
- Hey!

39
00:05:11,640 --> 00:05:12,880
- Does it hurt?
- Hey.

40
00:05:12,960 --> 00:05:14,360
If it hurts, slap me back.

41
00:05:14,440 --> 00:05:15,680
- Slap me back.
- What are you doing? Are you crazy?

42
00:05:15,760 --> 00:05:16,560
Slap me back.

43
00:05:16,640 --> 00:05:18,720
Go on. Slap me!

44
00:05:25,600 --> 00:05:27,080
What did you give me to drink?

45
00:05:53,400 --> 00:05:54,960
Well, if no one came, then no one came.

46
00:06:01,800 --> 00:06:03,240
Why would the Captain…?

47
00:06:03,960 --> 00:06:07,400
Did he have an urgent matter to deal with?
He didn't even call.

48
00:06:25,600 --> 00:06:27,080
Honestly,

49
00:06:27,600 --> 00:06:29,040
do we really have to go this far?

50
00:06:29,640 --> 00:06:33,360
Yes. We need to bring something with us.
It'll make things look more natural.

51
00:06:36,800 --> 00:06:37,920
This is what you call natural?

52
00:06:39,960 --> 00:06:41,040
What's unnatural about it?

53
00:06:42,080 --> 00:06:45,840
It's obvious we bought it.
We didn't make it ourselves.

54
00:06:45,920 --> 00:06:46,920
Oh?

55
00:06:47,000 --> 00:06:52,000
Just arrange it in a box. They won't
know whether it's bought or homemade.

56
00:06:54,720 --> 00:06:57,360
You're sure you won't change your mind?

57
00:06:58,080 --> 00:06:58,920
About what?

58
00:06:59,960 --> 00:07:02,800
About going to Mr. Sarut's house.

59
00:07:05,600 --> 00:07:09,720
Can you stop asking whether I'll
change my mind or whether I'll go or not.

60
00:07:09,800 --> 00:07:11,600
Please.

61
00:07:13,040 --> 00:07:17,160
Alright, alright.
I got it. I can't even ask a question.

62
00:07:19,600 --> 00:07:21,480
Wait. I've got an idea.

63
00:07:22,360 --> 00:07:23,360
What?

64
00:07:29,200 --> 00:07:30,560
Let's put it in this basket instead.

65
00:07:30,640 --> 00:07:33,600
Arrange it nicely. It'll match the pie.

66
00:07:34,680 --> 00:07:35,800
How is that? Am I smart?

67
00:07:36,800 --> 00:07:38,400
Very smart.

68
00:07:38,920 --> 00:07:39,760
Awesome.

69
00:07:39,840 --> 00:07:42,040
Of course. Try it. It's delicious.

70
00:07:42,640 --> 00:07:45,720
I made it myself. Anyone would believe it.

71
00:07:46,840 --> 00:07:49,720
See? Perfect match.

72
00:07:51,240 --> 00:07:53,880
So how's Chiang Mai?

73
00:07:53,960 --> 00:07:56,400
Are the sales meeting the targets we set?

74
00:07:56,480 --> 00:08:00,080
<i>With the utmost respect, ma'am,</i>
<i>the sales are slightly below target now.</i>

75
00:08:00,160 --> 00:08:03,080
<i>I think it might be because</i>
<i>the dust levels in the air are too high.</i>

76
00:08:05,000 --> 00:08:06,280
Just a moment, Supol.

77
00:08:12,760 --> 00:08:17,800
I said don't place things so close
to the edge. That's why they fall.

78
00:08:18,320 --> 00:08:20,720
Good thing the frame didn't shatter.

79
00:08:27,920 --> 00:08:29,680
What now?

80
00:08:29,760 --> 00:08:34,280
See? I said again and again.
They kept placing things precariously.

81
00:08:34,880 --> 00:08:39,000
Oh dear. My picture frame broke.

82
00:08:39,080 --> 00:08:40,880
Housekeeper.

83
00:08:40,960 --> 00:08:44,039
Who's there? Come here. Bring a broom too.

84
00:08:46,840 --> 00:08:48,800
What's going on now?

85
00:08:51,320 --> 00:08:54,320
What are you two doing, Rat, Kluay?

86
00:08:54,840 --> 00:08:58,040
What do you need?
Why didn't you call the housekeeper?

87
00:08:58,120 --> 00:09:00,280
Well, we…

88
00:09:00,880 --> 00:09:03,680
Well, we were

89
00:09:04,480 --> 00:09:06,200
making dessert.

90
00:09:06,280 --> 00:09:09,440
And suddenly, this happened.

91
00:09:11,120 --> 00:09:13,800
This house is full of coincidences.

92
00:09:13,880 --> 00:09:17,240
Just clean it yourselves
or call the housekeeper.

93
00:09:17,320 --> 00:09:18,480
Grandma,

94
00:09:18,560 --> 00:09:21,480
you should go back to work.
I'll take care of this.

95
00:09:22,760 --> 00:09:25,880
Earlier, I heard Kluay say

96
00:09:25,960 --> 00:09:28,480
you were making dessert.
Let me see. What kind of dessert?

97
00:09:29,080 --> 00:09:31,320
No, no need to look. It's…

98
00:09:31,840 --> 00:09:33,640
It's nothing.

99
00:09:33,720 --> 00:09:35,000
Why not?

100
00:09:35,080 --> 00:09:38,240
Why can't I see it? What dessert
did you make, and who is it for?

101
00:09:41,200 --> 00:09:42,320
It's for you, Grandma.

102
00:09:43,080 --> 00:09:44,920
- For me?
- Yes.

103
00:09:45,000 --> 00:09:49,520
Warat wanted to surprise you

104
00:09:49,600 --> 00:09:52,240
because he successfully
negotiated business in Taiwan.

105
00:09:52,840 --> 00:09:56,280
Oh my. You have that side of you too?

106
00:09:56,360 --> 00:09:57,960
I can't believe it.

107
00:09:58,760 --> 00:09:59,680
But anyway,

108
00:09:59,760 --> 00:10:05,080
at least you're staying home
instead of causing trouble outside.

109
00:10:05,160 --> 00:10:08,240
Yes, Grandma. You should go back to work.
It's hot here.

110
00:10:08,840 --> 00:10:12,680
Alright, alright.
You're really shooing me away.

111
00:10:12,760 --> 00:10:14,200
When the housekeeper comes,

112
00:10:14,280 --> 00:10:17,880
tell her to set
two more places at the dinner table.

113
00:10:18,480 --> 00:10:21,760
Is Mr. Supol coming for dinner with you?

114
00:10:21,840 --> 00:10:24,120
Supol will definitely be here.

115
00:10:24,200 --> 00:10:26,800
But the two extra seats
are actually for you two.

116
00:10:26,880 --> 00:10:30,160
Because Supol will come
to discuss work with me

117
00:10:30,240 --> 00:10:32,240
about the projects
in Singapore and Taiwan.

118
00:10:32,320 --> 00:10:35,720
I want both of you to stay and listen.

119
00:10:35,800 --> 00:10:36,920
Uh.

120
00:10:41,480 --> 00:10:42,400
What should we do now?

121
00:10:42,480 --> 00:10:46,120
If we have to have dinner with Grandma,
we can't go to Mr. Sarut's house.

122
00:10:51,640 --> 00:10:54,800
I know who did this.

123
00:10:55,880 --> 00:10:57,080
Who?

124
00:10:57,800 --> 00:10:58,800
Ms. Ampha, right?

125
00:11:00,520 --> 00:11:03,600
You don't want Kluay and me
to go to Mr. Sarut's house, do you?

126
00:11:06,240 --> 00:11:09,480
But I'm telling you right now.
I'm going no matter what.

127
00:11:11,640 --> 00:11:13,120
Did you hear that, Ms. Ampha?

128
00:11:17,520 --> 00:11:21,480
Anong, make sure
everything is neat and tidy.

129
00:11:21,560 --> 00:11:24,280
Anything messy
will be embarrassing for the guests.

130
00:11:24,880 --> 00:11:25,840
That one too.

131
00:11:29,280 --> 00:11:30,600
This one?

132
00:11:30,680 --> 00:11:32,640
Yes. Why?

133
00:11:33,400 --> 00:11:35,000
But this is Sin's photo.

134
00:11:35,080 --> 00:11:36,520
Exactly.

135
00:11:36,600 --> 00:11:39,560
You know they don't get along.

136
00:11:40,440 --> 00:11:42,680
How do you think
Sin would feel if he saw it?

137
00:11:42,760 --> 00:11:45,480
I didn't say to throw it away.

138
00:11:46,120 --> 00:11:48,560
When he goes,
just put it back where it was.

139
00:11:48,640 --> 00:11:49,680
That's it.

140
00:11:50,880 --> 00:11:52,080
Yes.

141
00:11:52,160 --> 00:11:53,200
Mm.

142
00:12:03,200 --> 00:12:04,520
What should I do

143
00:12:05,480 --> 00:12:07,560
to make Warat see the truth?

144
00:12:08,160 --> 00:12:09,040
See the truth?

145
00:12:09,920 --> 00:12:11,440
About what?

146
00:12:12,640 --> 00:12:16,400
About the Vanich family inheritance?

147
00:12:16,480 --> 00:12:18,760
No, not that.

148
00:12:18,840 --> 00:12:20,800
That can wait.

149
00:12:21,760 --> 00:12:23,400
What matters more

150
00:12:23,920 --> 00:12:25,080
is that girl Kluay.

151
00:12:29,560 --> 00:12:30,440
Kluay?

152
00:12:31,000 --> 00:12:33,440
Boonsita, the one
who keeps following Mr. Warat around?

153
00:12:33,520 --> 00:12:35,080
Yes. Exactly.

154
00:12:36,120 --> 00:12:39,960
If she keeps following him around,
and it goes as far as marriage

155
00:12:40,040 --> 00:12:43,160
and registering their marriage,
I'll faint.

156
00:12:44,000 --> 00:12:48,000
An orphan girl
with a well-bred man like Warat?

157
00:12:50,160 --> 00:12:53,480
So today,
Mr. Warat is bringing Kluay with him?

158
00:12:53,560 --> 00:12:56,080
Yes. He's bringing her.

159
00:12:57,040 --> 00:13:00,680
Since they're already coming today,
should we take this opportunity

160
00:13:01,720 --> 00:13:04,280
to talk to Warat and tell him directly?

161
00:13:17,840 --> 00:13:18,800
Why are you smiling?

162
00:13:23,280 --> 00:13:24,840
- Huh?
- Oh.

163
00:13:24,920 --> 00:13:27,240
I'm just listening to what you're saying.

164
00:13:27,320 --> 00:13:29,040
And I agree with you.

165
00:13:29,120 --> 00:13:31,720
You're right, Mr. Rut.

166
00:13:31,800 --> 00:13:33,320
Honestly,

167
00:13:33,400 --> 00:13:37,040
that girl Kluay is not worthy
of Mr. Warat at all.

168
00:13:37,600 --> 00:13:40,080
But you don't need to worry.

169
00:13:40,600 --> 00:13:45,320
That girl will never be able
to have Mr. Warat.

170
00:13:47,160 --> 00:13:48,440
You have a way?

171
00:13:49,920 --> 00:13:52,040
What could I possibly do?

172
00:13:53,400 --> 00:13:55,920
That girl is just digging her own grave.

173
00:13:57,960 --> 00:13:59,840
You're talking strangely.

174
00:14:02,080 --> 00:14:03,880
What nonsense are you saying?

175
00:14:10,640 --> 00:14:11,760
Oh, Captain.

176
00:14:13,040 --> 00:14:14,200
Hello, Captain.

177
00:14:16,160 --> 00:14:18,760
You disappeared
after making that appointment.

178
00:14:22,400 --> 00:14:23,400
What?

179
00:14:25,160 --> 00:14:26,760
A motorcycle accident?

180
00:14:27,920 --> 00:14:28,920
A heart attack?

181
00:14:30,000 --> 00:14:31,040
Hey…

182
00:14:37,240 --> 00:14:39,440
You can actually kill, huh?

183
00:14:42,280 --> 00:14:45,040
Anong, hurry up. They'll be here soon.

184
00:14:46,800 --> 00:14:47,800
Yes.

185
00:15:01,440 --> 00:15:02,320
Mr. Warat,

186
00:15:02,400 --> 00:15:07,280
maybe we should cancel the appointment
with Mr. Sarut or postpone it.

187
00:15:07,360 --> 00:15:09,000
Why should we do that?

188
00:15:09,080 --> 00:15:12,480
We're just having dinner with Grandma.
It's not like we're locked up.

189
00:15:13,000 --> 00:15:15,120
I can still make it
to Mr. Sarut's house in time.

190
00:15:15,720 --> 00:15:19,440
But I really don't see a way
for us to get away from your grandma.

191
00:15:19,520 --> 00:15:20,960
Our lives belong to us.

192
00:15:21,480 --> 00:15:23,560
If we're determined to do the right thing,

193
00:15:23,640 --> 00:15:26,000
no one can stop us,

194
00:15:27,240 --> 00:15:29,160
unless we're not truly determined.

195
00:15:30,360 --> 00:15:31,600
Remember what I said.

196
00:15:35,960 --> 00:15:37,840
If we don't make it in time,
it'll be because of you.

197
00:15:44,080 --> 00:15:44,920
Wow.

198
00:15:45,880 --> 00:15:47,320
You ordered so many dishes.

199
00:15:48,240 --> 00:15:49,080
They look delicious.

200
00:15:52,080 --> 00:15:56,520
I ordered a lot of special dishes.
There's still plenty more.

201
00:15:57,960 --> 00:15:59,720
- I'll finish all of them.
- Mm.

202
00:16:00,320 --> 00:16:01,160
Good.

203
00:16:03,000 --> 00:16:07,720
When you have time, we should
eat together like this more often.

204
00:16:09,360 --> 00:16:10,280
Yes.

205
00:16:11,640 --> 00:16:13,520
Besides making desserts,

206
00:16:13,600 --> 00:16:16,720
can you cook other things too?

207
00:16:17,800 --> 00:16:21,840
Well… I can cook a little.

208
00:16:22,720 --> 00:16:25,520
Good. Then cook for me sometime.

209
00:16:27,640 --> 00:16:32,280
Of course. Is there any particular dish
you'd like? I'll make it for you.

210
00:16:32,920 --> 00:16:36,520
Simple Thai dishes.

211
00:16:36,600 --> 00:16:40,320
I like curries, things like <i>kaeng kradang,</i>

212
00:16:41,120 --> 00:16:45,880
<i>kaeng rawaeng,</i> or <i>kaeng ranjuan.</i>
Simple dishes.

213
00:16:47,280 --> 00:16:48,560
Simple dishes?

214
00:16:51,080 --> 00:16:54,240
Or maybe some spicy salads.

215
00:16:55,280 --> 00:16:56,760
Spicy salads are my specialty.

216
00:16:56,840 --> 00:16:59,160
- Really? That's great.
- Yes.

217
00:16:59,240 --> 00:17:02,720
I like simple salads too.

218
00:17:02,800 --> 00:17:05,119
Like <i>yum yai, yum tawai,</i>

219
00:17:05,200 --> 00:17:09,040
or <i>saeng-wa.</i> Very easy dishes.
Can you make them?

220
00:17:09,640 --> 00:17:12,720
I don't know any of those.

221
00:17:13,280 --> 00:17:16,880
But the salad I'm best at
is glass noodle salad.

222
00:17:20,640 --> 00:17:23,640
Well, that's good actually.
You're honest about it.

223
00:17:24,160 --> 00:17:27,400
If you can do it, you say you can.
If you can't, you say you can't.

224
00:17:29,480 --> 00:17:31,280
Your mother Toi

225
00:17:31,360 --> 00:17:35,400
must have raised you very well.

226
00:17:36,120 --> 00:17:37,320
Thank you, Grandma.

227
00:17:37,400 --> 00:17:42,960
Mama Toi always taught me
to live with the truth. Because the truth

228
00:17:43,040 --> 00:17:45,240
is something sacred that will protect us.

229
00:17:50,040 --> 00:17:51,680
The food is delicious, Grandma.

230
00:17:51,760 --> 00:17:54,240
Good. Eat more.

231
00:17:55,520 --> 00:17:56,760
Hello, Mr. Arnon.

232
00:17:59,640 --> 00:18:02,280
About the provincial client's case?

233
00:18:03,520 --> 00:18:05,320
Okay, okay. I'll handle it.

234
00:18:06,200 --> 00:18:07,280
Okay.

235
00:18:19,680 --> 00:18:24,160
Seeing Warat
taking his work so seriously like this

236
00:18:24,240 --> 00:18:27,320
really reassures me.

237
00:18:28,640 --> 00:18:30,320
Come to think of it,

238
00:18:30,400 --> 00:18:32,200
you yourself

239
00:18:32,280 --> 00:18:34,920
probably help him a lot too, don't you?

240
00:18:35,000 --> 00:18:36,560
Am I right?

241
00:18:38,320 --> 00:18:40,560
- Well…
- Kluay.

242
00:18:40,640 --> 00:18:44,240
The client documents I asked you to keep,
where did you put them?

243
00:18:44,760 --> 00:18:46,400
The documents…

244
00:18:46,480 --> 00:18:47,680
The one I mentioned this evening.

245
00:18:49,120 --> 00:18:50,640
Go check for him.

246
00:18:50,720 --> 00:18:52,160
Oh, right.

247
00:18:52,680 --> 00:18:54,320
I told you to store them properly.

248
00:18:54,400 --> 00:18:55,920
- Yes.
- You've forgotten several times already.

249
00:18:56,000 --> 00:18:58,200
I can't find them.

250
00:19:02,960 --> 00:19:04,120
Come here.

251
00:19:04,720 --> 00:19:05,640
The documents.

252
00:19:16,600 --> 00:19:19,120
Are you really going to do this?

253
00:19:19,200 --> 00:19:20,840
I don't feel good about it.

254
00:19:20,920 --> 00:19:23,480
Kluay, I already told you

255
00:19:23,560 --> 00:19:25,440
what we do is our business.

256
00:19:25,960 --> 00:19:27,080
Hey.

257
00:19:27,160 --> 00:19:29,760
But saying that sounds selfish.

258
00:19:29,840 --> 00:19:31,720
That's your grandma.

259
00:19:31,800 --> 00:19:33,600
How could you just leave her like that?

260
00:19:33,680 --> 00:19:37,520
Do you really think
my grandma can't see through me?

261
00:19:38,800 --> 00:19:39,840
This time,

262
00:19:40,360 --> 00:19:42,880
she's just playing along with my game.

263
00:19:43,840 --> 00:19:45,840
What do you mean? I don't understand.

264
00:19:47,800 --> 00:19:51,320
Someone like my grandma
would never fall for something so simple.

265
00:19:51,840 --> 00:19:54,800
We've played many rounds
of this game already.

266
00:19:55,680 --> 00:19:57,960
The more you explain,
the more confused I get.

267
00:19:59,040 --> 00:20:02,800
If you're confused, don't overthink it.
Let's focus on one thing at a time.

268
00:20:02,880 --> 00:20:06,440
Right now, we focus
only on Mr. Sarut and Ms. Anong.

269
00:20:08,600 --> 00:20:09,880
Remember this.

270
00:20:10,680 --> 00:20:12,360
If at any point, you don't feel alright,

271
00:20:13,400 --> 00:20:14,840
just tell me.

272
00:20:15,440 --> 00:20:17,880
We'll step back. That's all.

273
00:20:18,880 --> 00:20:20,360
I'll endure it.

274
00:20:20,880 --> 00:20:23,680
This isn't something you have to endure.

275
00:20:24,440 --> 00:20:26,360
But it's worth enduring.

276
00:20:26,440 --> 00:20:28,840
If we go this time
and get all the answers we need,

277
00:20:28,920 --> 00:20:31,320
we won't have to
investigate anything else.

278
00:20:31,400 --> 00:20:34,360
I'll endure it as long as I can,

279
00:20:35,480 --> 00:20:36,800
but I won't force myself.

280
00:20:36,880 --> 00:20:40,120
If I can't handle it anymore,
I'll tell you, okay? Don't worry.

281
00:20:47,680 --> 00:20:49,240
Promise me one thing.

282
00:20:50,440 --> 00:20:52,840
If you see any strange signs,

283
00:20:54,520 --> 00:20:55,720
you must tell me.

284
00:20:57,760 --> 00:20:58,800
Alright.

285
00:21:11,080 --> 00:21:12,160
You promised.

286
00:21:13,200 --> 00:21:14,680
Your safety

287
00:21:15,720 --> 00:21:16,920
comes first.

288
00:21:20,000 --> 00:21:21,120
Yes.

289
00:21:21,200 --> 00:21:25,000
"Our safety" comes first.

290
00:22:04,320 --> 00:22:05,400
Mr. Sarut,

291
00:22:06,600 --> 00:22:08,560
I want to apologize for being rude before.

292
00:22:09,680 --> 00:22:11,120
I really regret it.

293
00:22:13,480 --> 00:22:17,560
Oh, no need to bow like that.
You don't have to apologize so seriously.

294
00:22:18,120 --> 00:22:19,120
I understand.

295
00:22:19,880 --> 00:22:22,000
People make mistakes.

296
00:22:23,040 --> 00:22:24,560
And I've

297
00:22:25,320 --> 00:22:27,200
never held it against you.

298
00:22:29,640 --> 00:22:33,480
As long as nothing is unresolved,
that puts my mind at ease.

299
00:22:35,800 --> 00:22:39,000
Alright, let's not waste time
talking about the past.

300
00:22:39,080 --> 00:22:41,320
We've finally arranged to meet.

301
00:22:42,120 --> 00:22:43,000
Are you hungry yet?

302
00:22:43,600 --> 00:22:44,680
We can start eating now.

303
00:22:47,160 --> 00:22:48,200
Anong,

304
00:22:48,280 --> 00:22:50,320
is the food ready?
You can bring it to the table now.

305
00:22:51,160 --> 00:22:52,120
Yes.

306
00:22:53,200 --> 00:22:54,680
Then I'll go help carry it.

307
00:22:54,760 --> 00:22:55,720
No need.

308
00:22:59,080 --> 00:23:02,000
You're a guest. Please sit.

309
00:23:05,200 --> 00:23:06,960
Just a moment, Mr. Warat.

310
00:23:12,640 --> 00:23:13,840
Som,

311
00:23:13,920 --> 00:23:16,880
come take this cloth
as a spare for Mr. Arnon.

312
00:23:20,720 --> 00:23:21,680
Som?

313
00:23:22,400 --> 00:23:24,400
Som, are you in Kluay's room?

314
00:23:27,560 --> 00:23:28,480
Som?

315
00:23:37,440 --> 00:23:39,280
What was that sound?

316
00:23:44,520 --> 00:23:45,640
Why is it like this?

317
00:23:54,600 --> 00:23:55,760
What is this?

318
00:24:05,840 --> 00:24:07,360
Uh…

319
00:24:08,720 --> 00:24:09,680
Are you…

320
00:24:12,360 --> 00:24:14,160
Ms. Mysterious?

321
00:24:21,640 --> 00:24:22,920
There's nothing here.

322
00:24:23,600 --> 00:24:25,240
I'm overthinking it.

323
00:24:36,640 --> 00:24:38,280
- Please try it.
- Thank you.

324
00:24:42,200 --> 00:24:43,200
Mr. Sarut, Ms. Anong,

325
00:24:44,800 --> 00:24:46,800
you seem like very kind people.

326
00:24:47,880 --> 00:24:49,880
Jirasin is lucky

327
00:24:49,960 --> 00:24:52,160
to have such a warm family.

328
00:24:53,920 --> 00:24:56,000
We just support each other as best we can.

329
00:24:56,600 --> 00:25:01,400
It took a lot to reach this point,
and I'm very proud of Sin.

330
00:25:01,480 --> 00:25:03,480
Because actually,

331
00:25:03,560 --> 00:25:06,160
Sin only has one relative left,
which is me.

332
00:25:06,680 --> 00:25:08,520
His father, mother,

333
00:25:09,520 --> 00:25:12,840
and younger sister have all passed away.

334
00:25:16,000 --> 00:25:16,960
By the way,

335
00:25:17,920 --> 00:25:19,240
Ms. Kluay,

336
00:25:19,880 --> 00:25:21,720
you were friends with Lak, right?

337
00:25:23,880 --> 00:25:24,800
Yes.

338
00:25:26,080 --> 00:25:28,880
If Lak were still alive,

339
00:25:29,760 --> 00:25:32,800
she would probably be
an architect like you.

340
00:25:35,920 --> 00:25:38,560
Lak was very dedicated.

341
00:25:39,080 --> 00:25:43,080
Every project she worked on in college
came out excellent.

342
00:25:45,320 --> 00:25:46,840
I'm

343
00:25:47,400 --> 00:25:48,680
sorry for your loss.

344
00:25:49,520 --> 00:25:51,560
When Sin sees you,

345
00:25:52,760 --> 00:25:55,480
he probably can't help thinking of Lak.

346
00:25:56,520 --> 00:25:57,880
Just like I do.

347
00:26:03,040 --> 00:26:04,160
Ms. Anong.

348
00:26:06,360 --> 00:26:07,480
Yes?

349
00:26:08,320 --> 00:26:10,960
You've been looking
like you want to ask something.

350
00:26:13,200 --> 00:26:15,560
Well, I heard that

351
00:26:16,120 --> 00:26:18,680
my mother knew Jirasin's father.

352
00:26:19,360 --> 00:26:23,520
And you're Jirasin's aunt,
so you probably knew my mother too, right?

353
00:26:25,600 --> 00:26:26,640
Yes.

354
00:26:31,640 --> 00:26:35,040
Ms. Praewilai was a very beautiful woman

355
00:26:35,120 --> 00:26:37,720
and extremely kind.

356
00:26:40,120 --> 00:26:41,080
I…

357
00:26:42,840 --> 00:26:44,680
really like hearing stories
about my mother.

358
00:26:48,400 --> 00:26:51,240
But not many people tell me about her.

359
00:26:52,040 --> 00:26:54,080
When my father was still alive,

360
00:26:55,400 --> 00:26:57,000
he would tell me about her sometimes.

361
00:26:59,520 --> 00:27:00,960
But since he passed away,

362
00:27:02,520 --> 00:27:04,280
no one really talks about her anymore.

363
00:27:05,800 --> 00:27:07,840
Mrs. Wanee must be busy
with work all the time, right?

364
00:27:08,880 --> 00:27:09,960
Yes.

365
00:27:12,160 --> 00:27:15,920
The anniversary of my mother's death
is coming soon.

366
00:27:17,520 --> 00:27:19,040
I just miss her.

367
00:27:19,960 --> 00:27:21,120
Mr. Warat,

368
00:27:23,520 --> 00:27:27,200
if there's anything you want to know
about Ms. Prae,

369
00:27:28,120 --> 00:27:29,720
if I know it,

370
00:27:31,440 --> 00:27:32,880
I'll answer you.

371
00:27:39,280 --> 00:27:40,480
I want to know…

372
00:27:43,800 --> 00:27:44,880
how she died.

373
00:27:49,720 --> 00:27:52,200
It might sound like a big question, but…

374
00:27:54,400 --> 00:27:56,960
all the information I've gotten
from people is inconsistent.

375
00:27:57,480 --> 00:28:01,120
No one seems to tell the truth.

376
00:28:01,200 --> 00:28:03,280
Some say my mother fainted

377
00:28:03,360 --> 00:28:05,320
and fell from the building. Others say…

378
00:28:07,080 --> 00:28:09,560
she committed suicide.

379
00:28:14,040 --> 00:28:15,200
Well.

380
00:28:15,960 --> 00:28:19,200
This matter is quite sensitive.

381
00:28:20,800 --> 00:28:23,360
If it were anything else about Ms. Prae,

382
00:28:24,160 --> 00:28:28,400
I might be able to answer.

383
00:28:28,480 --> 00:28:32,320
But about this, I'm afraid I can't…

384
00:28:32,400 --> 00:28:33,520
Mr. Rut.

385
00:28:34,800 --> 00:28:36,280
I think

386
00:28:36,360 --> 00:28:39,720
Mr. Warat is old enough
to hear the truth now.

387
00:28:41,480 --> 00:28:42,680
You mean

388
00:28:44,360 --> 00:28:46,600
you're going to tell me the truth?

389
00:28:49,440 --> 00:28:52,040
Do you really want to hear it?

390
00:28:58,360 --> 00:28:59,440
That day…

391
00:29:03,440 --> 00:29:05,040
My mom committed suicide?

392
00:29:07,800 --> 00:29:10,960
Actually,
I followed the news about it back then.

393
00:29:12,160 --> 00:29:14,120
Personally,
I don't think she killed herself.

394
00:29:15,880 --> 00:29:16,760
Mr. Warat,

395
00:29:17,800 --> 00:29:20,240
I think you shouldn't think like that.

396
00:29:23,000 --> 00:29:24,600
Actually,

397
00:29:24,680 --> 00:29:27,080
a long time has passed since then.

398
00:29:27,760 --> 00:29:32,000
Some details may have
become unclear. However,

399
00:29:32,880 --> 00:29:37,560
there's one thing I can confirm.
Ms. Praewilai, your mother,

400
00:29:38,400 --> 00:29:40,720
was a beautiful woman

401
00:29:40,800 --> 00:29:43,960
with a very kind heart.

402
00:29:48,160 --> 00:29:49,240
Thank you.

403
00:29:52,200 --> 00:29:54,080
Please continue your conversation.

404
00:29:54,160 --> 00:29:56,360
I'll excuse myself to refill the water.

405
00:29:56,440 --> 00:29:58,800
I can do it for you.

406
00:30:32,920 --> 00:30:34,440
Thank you.

407
00:30:37,960 --> 00:30:39,720
If I had known that you two

408
00:30:41,280 --> 00:30:44,040
knew my mother, I would've talked

409
00:30:44,120 --> 00:30:45,880
with you both long ago.

410
00:30:47,520 --> 00:30:51,200
If you were that close to my mother,

411
00:30:51,280 --> 00:30:54,480
then we're practically relatives.

412
00:30:55,080 --> 00:30:58,280
Wichan was my close friend.

413
00:30:59,400 --> 00:31:00,800
And Praewilai,

414
00:31:01,320 --> 00:31:05,280
I naturally became
familiar with her as well.

415
00:31:07,440 --> 00:31:09,800
If you both knew my mother,

416
00:31:10,560 --> 00:31:11,760
then…

417
00:31:14,240 --> 00:31:18,360
do you happen to know Pong and Soi?

418
00:31:19,640 --> 00:31:22,760
<i>Your son Ton is such a cute boy.</i>

419
00:31:24,040 --> 00:31:26,080
Why are you making such a gloomy face?

420
00:31:26,160 --> 00:31:28,240
I was just complimenting your child.

421
00:31:30,520 --> 00:31:33,320
Please, leave my son alone.

422
00:31:33,880 --> 00:31:36,640
I'm already paying back the money
I took from you.

423
00:31:36,720 --> 00:31:39,240
I already told you
I don't want the money back.

424
00:31:41,200 --> 00:31:44,920
Bring Ampha and Waree,
her daughter, to me right now.

425
00:31:46,320 --> 00:31:49,360
As for Pong and Soi,

426
00:31:50,040 --> 00:31:51,680
they used to work here.

427
00:31:51,760 --> 00:31:54,080
But they quit a long time ago.

428
00:31:55,160 --> 00:31:57,920
I hear they won the lottery,
a big jackpot.

429
00:31:58,000 --> 00:32:00,040
Then they moved overseas.

430
00:32:00,880 --> 00:32:03,200
Isn't that right, Anong?
You told me that before, didn't you?

431
00:32:05,440 --> 00:32:08,840
I only heard it from the workers.

432
00:32:08,920 --> 00:32:12,360
I wasn't close to them,
so I don't actually know

433
00:32:12,440 --> 00:32:15,000
- what the real truth was.
- Right.

434
00:32:22,600 --> 00:32:23,440
They won the lottery

435
00:32:24,920 --> 00:32:26,840
and moved abroad?

436
00:32:30,080 --> 00:32:31,960
If it were me, I'd do the same.

437
00:32:34,720 --> 00:32:38,040
But why are you asking about those two?

438
00:32:38,120 --> 00:32:39,960
Oh, it's nothing.

439
00:32:40,040 --> 00:32:43,720
I just thought they were
people of the house for a long time,

440
00:32:44,240 --> 00:32:45,960
so I was curious. Nothing special.

441
00:32:50,680 --> 00:32:52,960
Hey, what are you doing?

442
00:32:53,520 --> 00:32:55,760
Refilling water.
I'm too lazy to walk over there.

443
00:32:56,960 --> 00:32:59,080
It's just over here.
I'll do it. Give it to me.

444
00:32:59,160 --> 00:33:01,160
- Just a little. Why are you being stingy?
- Hm.

445
00:33:01,240 --> 00:33:03,200
I'm not stingy. It's my glass.

446
00:33:03,280 --> 00:33:05,160
- Hey.
- I'll go get it.

447
00:33:13,800 --> 00:33:16,840
Young people these days
really talk so sweetly to each other.

448
00:33:28,040 --> 00:33:30,160
Anyway, today I must thank you

449
00:33:30,240 --> 00:33:32,080
both very much.

450
00:33:32,160 --> 00:33:34,320
The food was really delicious.

451
00:33:34,400 --> 00:33:36,760
I envy that Jirasin

452
00:33:36,840 --> 00:33:39,360
gets to eat food like this every day.

453
00:33:40,480 --> 00:33:42,040
What's there to envy?

454
00:33:42,120 --> 00:33:44,160
You're an important guest, Mr. Warat.

455
00:33:44,240 --> 00:33:46,480
You can come anytime.
You're always welcome here.

456
00:33:47,000 --> 00:33:51,840
Think of this house as your second home.

457
00:33:52,520 --> 00:33:56,160
Next time,
I'll show you my cooking skills too.

458
00:33:56,240 --> 00:33:59,320
This time, Ms. Anong cooked
everything alone. I feel bad about it.

459
00:33:59,920 --> 00:34:01,000
It was tiring, but worth it.

460
00:34:02,560 --> 00:34:03,560
What do you mean?

461
00:34:05,200 --> 00:34:09,120
I mean getting to sit
and chat about this and that

462
00:34:09,199 --> 00:34:10,120
is worth it.

463
00:34:11,920 --> 00:34:12,920
Right.

464
00:34:17,400 --> 00:34:19,280
The flowers
are blooming beautifully this time.

465
00:34:20,600 --> 00:34:21,920
They smell wonderful.

466
00:34:23,080 --> 00:34:26,280
You're not allergic like last time.
I'm glad.

467
00:34:46,679 --> 00:34:49,520
Maybe we suspected Ms. Anong for nothing.

468
00:34:49,600 --> 00:34:50,679
No.

469
00:34:51,360 --> 00:34:54,480
She's different behind people's backs.
So insincere.

470
00:34:56,280 --> 00:35:01,360
But I think Mr. Sarut seems different.
He seems very kind, especially to you.

471
00:35:02,360 --> 00:35:05,520
No, I think he has double standards.

472
00:35:05,600 --> 00:35:06,920
With you,

473
00:35:07,000 --> 00:35:08,680
he barely speaks a word.

474
00:35:10,920 --> 00:35:12,680
Yes, I felt that too.

475
00:35:17,560 --> 00:35:18,480
What's wrong?

476
00:35:19,640 --> 00:35:21,600
Nothing. Let's go.

477
00:35:21,680 --> 00:35:22,880
Let's get inside.

478
00:35:34,480 --> 00:35:35,560
Mr. Warat.

479
00:35:37,280 --> 00:35:39,120
Hey! Kluay!

480
00:35:39,200 --> 00:35:43,160
Did you enjoy that? Running away
from the dining table like children.

481
00:35:43,240 --> 00:35:45,160
- Oh my goodness.
- Kluay!

482
00:35:45,240 --> 00:35:47,800
Grandma, tell Mr. Supol
to call a doctor immediately.

483
00:35:47,880 --> 00:35:48,920
Kluay!

484
00:35:49,000 --> 00:35:49,840
Kluay, get up.

485
00:35:51,480 --> 00:35:52,800
- Get up.
- Kluay.

486
00:35:53,320 --> 00:35:54,680
What's going on?

487
00:35:59,520 --> 00:36:00,840
Arnon really left already.

488
00:36:01,360 --> 00:36:03,240
Of course, he did.
Did you think I was joking?

489
00:36:03,760 --> 00:36:07,320
I didn't think that.
But how is this possible? Poisoning?

490
00:36:07,880 --> 00:36:11,920
Possible or not, it already happened.
I don't spread false news.

491
00:36:13,200 --> 00:36:14,680
Then who would poison him?

492
00:36:16,640 --> 00:36:20,400
Don't mop anything up.
I told you. Don't clean it.

493
00:36:20,480 --> 00:36:21,360
Go back.

494
00:36:22,920 --> 00:36:27,000
Rat, why won't you let
the housekeeper clean it up?

495
00:36:27,080 --> 00:36:31,200
Grandma, it's evidence
of what happened to Kluay.

496
00:36:31,280 --> 00:36:35,440
Are you sure Kluay was poisoned
the same way Arnon was?

497
00:36:35,520 --> 00:36:37,920
Why hasn't the ambulance arrived yet?

498
00:36:41,200 --> 00:36:43,400
I think I'll take Kluay
to the hospital myself.

499
00:36:43,480 --> 00:36:44,760
- Kluay, let's go.
- You can't.

500
00:36:44,840 --> 00:36:46,920
I said you can't.

501
00:36:47,000 --> 00:36:50,560
Think about it,
what if something happens on the way?

502
00:36:51,440 --> 00:36:52,640
But the ambulance isn't here yet.

503
00:36:52,720 --> 00:36:56,000
Just wait a little longer. Calm down.

504
00:36:56,600 --> 00:36:57,720
Kluay, are you okay?

505
00:36:58,240 --> 00:37:00,360
I shouldn't have brought you
into something like this.

506
00:37:02,400 --> 00:37:05,440
Running around
asking everyone for help like this

507
00:37:05,960 --> 00:37:07,840
might not help Kluay at all.

508
00:37:10,040 --> 00:37:12,840
The fact that the two of you
were able to connect today

509
00:37:13,440 --> 00:37:15,240
means there must be a bond.

510
00:37:15,760 --> 00:37:18,160
The bond between you and Kluay.

511
00:37:18,760 --> 00:37:20,360
<i>That is the answer.</i>

512
00:37:28,960 --> 00:37:29,960
Kluay.

513
00:37:30,040 --> 00:37:31,800
Kluay!

514
00:37:32,400 --> 00:37:33,600
Hey, anyone.

515
00:37:33,680 --> 00:37:35,880
Call any car. Now.

516
00:37:36,560 --> 00:37:37,800
Kluay, get up.

517
00:37:38,400 --> 00:37:41,480
Boonsita.
Boonsita, you have to be alright.

518
00:37:41,560 --> 00:37:44,040
With the utmost respect, Mr. Warat,
the ambulance has arrived.

519
00:37:44,120 --> 00:37:45,720
Mr. Supol, hurry.

520
00:37:46,760 --> 00:37:47,960
Boonsita.

521
00:37:48,040 --> 00:37:50,040
Boonsita, you must be alright.

522
00:37:53,880 --> 00:37:57,160
<i>Be careful.</i>
<i>This might be the end of your time.</i>

523
00:38:04,880 --> 00:38:07,360
Both Ms. Kluay and Mr. Arnon
experienced similar incidents like this.

524
00:38:07,440 --> 00:38:09,640
From now on, we can't
trust anyone anymore, Mr. Warat.

525
00:38:09,720 --> 00:38:11,640
NEXT EPISODE

526
00:38:11,720 --> 00:38:14,360
What did you do to Kluay?
What did you do to Arnon?

527
00:38:14,440 --> 00:38:17,080
What did you do to them? Tell me.
What did you do to them?

528
00:38:20,000 --> 00:38:22,960
If something is beyond our control,

529
00:38:23,040 --> 00:38:24,680
there's nothing we can do anyway.

530
00:38:26,200 --> 00:38:28,440
Do you want Warat and me
to turn against each other?

531
